Q1 What is your understanding of Blockchain?
A1 Blockchain is a chain which contains different blocks and each block contain data whihc is distributed and encrypted. And the data stored is verifiable, unchangeable,
   tamperproof & Immutable
Q2 What is the core problem blockchain is trying to solve?
A2 Data Loss, Data Security, Data Corruption
Q3 What are the few features that Blockchain will give you?
A3 Immutability, Decentralized technology, Enhanced Security, Distributed ledger
Q4 What all things a Block contains?
A4 Block Number, Transaction record, Previous Block Signature, Mining key
Q5 How is the verifiability of Blockchain is been attained ?
A5 Due to its distributed database in which data is tamper proof.
